BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Tween Crafternoon
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260507T221500Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260507T233000Z
UID:68a37e20709d27410037bafa@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Tweens ages 10-14 are welcome to join us and create a new art
  or craft project the 1st Thursday of each month!\nMarch 5: Perler Party
 \nApril 2:  Yarn Landscapes\nMay 7:  Design your own Zine
LOCATION:Banks Public Library\, Jane Moore Community Room
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/68a37e20709d27410037bafa
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Makerspace Open Lab
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260415T003000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260415T023000Z
UID:699f9fb58b29ea2800d28bc8@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Makerspace Open Labs are for anyone who wants to check out the
  space and use our equipment to make cool things. Room assistants are avai
 lable to guide you in the basic use of the tools and technology. Come in w
 ith an idea and leave with a finished project! For more information about 
 the Makerspace and its resources\,\nsee here\n.\nMakerspace Open Labs take
  place on the following weekly schedule:\nTuesdays\n\, 5:30 - 7:30PM\nThur
 sdays\n\, 4:00 - 6:00PM\nSaturdays\n\, 10:00 AM - 1:00PM\nSundays\n\, 1:30
  - 5:30P\nEach month we provide the materials\, tools and instructions for
  a featured Makerspace project that everyone is invited to try.\nApril's f
 eatured project is Seed Paper (pictured).\nIMPORTANT:\nAdults using the M
 akerspace for the first time need to\nsign a waiver\n\; people under the a
 ge of 18 must have a waiver signed by a parent or guardian.\nYou can sign 
 and submit waivers online here.
LOCATION:Tualatin Public Library\, Makerspace
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/699f9fb58b29ea2800d28bc8
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
