BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Digital Navigator One on One Tech Help
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260429T170000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260429T190000Z
UID:68f17e4861706d28001e190b@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Digital Navigator One-On-One Tech Help each Wednesday from 10:
 00 a.m. -12:00 p.m. in the library. Need help with digital questions or jo
 b searches? This free program is in partnership with American Connection C
 orps & The Washington County Cooperative Library Services. Call the librar
 y at 503 324-1382 to schedule a session.\nIf no appointments are scheduled
  drop in tech help will be available.\nThe Digital Navigator Program (DNP)
  is a free service made possible by a partnership\nbetween Washington Coun
 ty Cooperative Library Services (WCCLS) and the Washington\nCounty Broadba
 nd Action Team. The DNP is funded in part by American Connections\nCorps\,
  an AmeriCorps program dedicated to advancing economic prosperity by bridg
 ing\nthe digital divide. This project is being supported\, in part\, by fe
 deral award number\nSLFRP0228 awarded to Washington County by the U.S. Dep
 artment of the Treasury.
LOCATION:Banks Public Library
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/68f17e4861706d28001e190b
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Tech Help
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260407T190000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260407T200000Z
UID:69af54c5b0595799c0a1ffcb@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Tech Help Tuesdays 12:00- 2:00p.m.\nDo you want to learn more 
 about using your phone\, tablet\, laptop or other device? Reserve your spo
 t for a one-on-one tech troubleshooting session and bring your devices or 
 use the library computers. You can receive help with creating\, saving\, a
 nd sharing documents\, composing & sending emails\, navigating the interne
 t\, using dictation or text-to-speech\, and other basic computer skills. T
 his is a free program. Sign up for a 1-hour appointment or by calling the 
 library at 503-647-5051 or visiting\nhttps://www.wccls.org/events\nDrop in
  appointments may be available
LOCATION:North Plains Public Library
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69af54c5b0595799c0a1ffcb
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:One Book\, One Coast
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260417T013000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260417T030000Z
UID:698655718b29ea2800ce6913@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a library program uniting a network of West Coast 
 Libraries in a shared celebration of literacy\, learning\, community and c
 ivil discourse.\nThe One Book\, One Coast 2026 chosen title is "They Calle
 d Us the Enemy" by George Takei.  We will kick off this program by explor
 ing the traditional Japanese method of fish printing called Gyotaku (don't
  worry\, we're not using real fish!).  We will have copies of the book av
 ailable to hand out at the art event.  Later\, we will discuss the book a
 nd attend a live-stream author talk with George Takei.\nThursday April 16:
   Gyotaku Fish Printing and book handout\nTeen group 3:15pm-4:30pm\nAdult
  group 6:30pm-8:00pm\nThursday May 28:  Book Discussion\nTeen group 3:15p
 m-4:30pm\nAdult group 6:30pm-8:00pm\nSunday May 31:  Live-Stream Author T
 alk with George Takei\n2:00pm-4:00pm
LOCATION:Banks Public Library\, Jane Moore Community Room
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/698655718b29ea2800ce6913
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
