UID:6983d58e8ef687c592a6fdb5@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:¡Hablemos Español! Join our engaging Spanish Conversation Cl
 ub at the library\, tailored for individuals eager to transition from stud
 ying to speaking. Facilitated by native speakers\, this program provides a
  welcoming space to practice conversational skills\, build confidence\, an
 d connect with fellow learners. No prior registration required - simply dr
 op in and let's start talking en Español!
LOCATION:Beaverton City Library\, Cathy Stanton Conference Room
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6983d58e8ef687c592a6fdb5
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Read to the Dogs/Lee a los perros
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260423T233000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260424T000000Z
UID:6932400076261f28005d8d91@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Want to build your skills and confidence? Read aloud to a trai
 ned therapy dog (accompanied by their handler) in a private 20-minute sess
 ion. Grades K – 12.\n¿Quieres mejorar tus habilidades y tu confianza? I
 nscríbete para leer en voz alta a perros de terapia (acompañados por un 
 entrenador) en una sesión privada de 20 minutos. K – 12o grado.\nYou ma
 y sign up for one(1) Read to the Dogs session within a one(1) month period
 .
LOCATION:Hillsboro Public Library\, Brookwood
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6932400076261f28005d8d91
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
