BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Digital Navigator – One-on-One Tech Help/ Navegador Digital – 
 Apoyo Uno a Uno
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260416T173000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260417T010000Z
UID:699ce8ca8b29ea2800d206aa@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Do you have questions about how to use a mobile phone or a com
 puter? Do you need help setting up a social media account? Schedule a 45-m
 inute appointment to receive technology assistance with a Digital Navigato
 r at the Shute Park Library or the Brookwood Library! Spanish-language su
 pport available only at the Shute Park Library.\nVisit our website at\nLib
 rary Bookings - Hillsboro Public Library\nor call\n503-615-6500\nto check 
 appointment availability.\n¿Tienes preguntas sobre cómo usar un teléfon
 o móvil o una computadora? ¿Necesitas ayuda para configurar una cuenta e
 n redes sociales? ¡Agenda una cita de 45 minutos para obtener asistencia 
 tecnológica con un Navegador Digital en la Biblioteca de Shute Park o la 
 Biblioteca de Brookwood!\nConsulta nuestro sitio web\nLibrary Bookings - H
 illsboro Public Library\no llama al\n503-615-6500\npara conocer la disponi
 bilidad de citas. Soporte en español disponible sólo en la Biblioteca de
  Shute Park.
LOCATION:Hillsboro Public Library\, Shute Park
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/699ce8ca8b29ea2800d206aa
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Makerspace Open Lab
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T203000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260316T003000Z
UID:699522474dacf581ff7c0b46@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Makerspace Open Labs are for anyone who wants to check out the
  space and use our equipment to make cool things. Room assistants are avai
 lable to guide you in the basic use of the tools and technology. Come in w
 ith an idea and leave with a finished project! For more information about 
 the Makerspace and its resources\,\nsee here\n.\nMakerspace Open Labs take
  place on the following weekly schedule:\nTuesdays\n\, 5:30 - 7:30PM\nThur
 sdays\n\, 4:00 - 6:00PM\nSaturdays\n\, 10:00 AM - 1:00PM\nSundays\n\, 1:30
  - 5:30P\nEach month we provide the materials\, tools and instructions for
  a featured Makerspace project that everyone is invited to try.\nMarch's f
 eatured project is Recycled Shrinky Dink Jewelry (pictured).\nIMPORTANT:\n
 Adults using the Makerspace for the first time need to\nsign a waiver\n\; 
 people under the age of 18 must have a waiver signed by a parent or guardi
 an.\nYou can sign and submit waivers online here.
LOCATION:Tualatin Public Library\, Makerspace
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/699522474dacf581ff7c0b46
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
