UID:688a54b9639e1e9694a3d692@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Whether you're a beginner trying to navigate your first smartp
 hone or a more experienced user looking to troubleshoot an issue with your
  computer or assemble a custom PC build\, we’re here to help. Drop-in to
  ask questions and receive one-on-one assistance with a variety of topics\
 , including but not limited to:\nBasic computer skills (e.g. how to use a 
 mouse\, open and close programs\, create and save documents)\nSetting up a
 nd using an email account\nUsing search engines and the internet\nTransfer
 ring files and photos between devices\nBasic smartphone and tablet skills 
 (e.g. how to make a call\, send a text message\, install and use an app)\n
 No matter your level of experience\, we welcome you to join us! No registr
 ation required. Please bring your device with you if you have one\, as thi
 s will allow us to better assist you with any specific issues you may be e
 xperiencing.
LOCATION:Aloha Community Library
