DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260509T220000Z
UID:689d3bc73bd870fbefa81031@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Need Help Tracing Your Ancestry?\nThe Genealogical Society of 
 Washington County\, Oregon\, helps in researching lost relatives! Bring as
  much information as possible about names (including maiden names)\, birth
  dates/locations\, marriage details\, and your family tree (digital or pri
 nted). You are welcome to bring your laptop if you own one\, as there is a
 ccess to electrical outlets and free Wi-Fi. You can easily access several 
 genealogy subscription databases for free while in the library\, such as t
 he Library Edition of Ancestry.\nPre-register by Wednesday before the sess
 ion to ensure we have enough volunteers.\nEmail:\nGSWCO2123@gmail.com
LOCATION:Hillsboro Public Library\, Brookwood
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/689d3bc73bd870fbefa81031
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
