BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Writer's Group: Workshop - Mining our Memories for Ideas
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260325T013000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260325T030000Z
UID:69a7ad9db0595799c0a0c9a2@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:This month's guest speaker is author Mindy Hardwick\, who will
  speak about "Mining our Memories for Ideas".\nThis workshop explores how
  we can use our memories to create compelling characters with both interna
 l and external character arcs. It includes prompts for generative writing 
 and draws on my own experience with both my memoir and a middle grade chil
 dren's book entitled\, The World Is a Sniff.\nAbout our presenter:\nMindy 
 Hardwick\nis the author of  small town romance\, children's books (ages 
 8-12) and have published a memoir\, Kids in Orange Voices From Juvenile De
 tention based on my experience facilitating a poetry workshop in a juvenil
 e detention. She is a member of the Rose City Romance Writers Chapter.\nT
 his is an in-person event. Please register so we know how many handouts t
 o have on hand.
LOCATION:Garden Home Community Library\, This event will be held in the li
 brary's event room (GeRoom #7)\, which is next to the locker rooms. Enter 
 the building via the main entrance and walk through the building to get to
  the room.
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a7ad9db0595799c0a0c9a2
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
