UID:69ab219019c54125aa02a084@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Watercolor Wednesday\, the 2nd Wednesday of each month from 5
 :00-6:30 p.m. in the library\,\na monthly meetup for anyone who wants to e
 xplore watercolor as a \nrelaxing practice and connect with other communit
 y members. Join us the 2\nnd\nWednesday of each month for a mid-week wind 
 down. Take a breath\, grab a\n brush\, and fill the page with color at thi
 s laid-back monthly \nwatercolor meetup. We’ll offer a simple project to
  try if you’d like\, or\n you can just paint freely and unwind. No press
 ure\, no perfection—just \ntime to chill and create.\nThis program is in
 tended for adults \nand teens\, no formal instruction provided. Drop in\, 
 no registration \nneeded but space is limited\, supplies provided or bring
  your own.
LOCATION:North Plains Public Library\, 31334 NW Commercial St\, North Plai
 ns\, OR 97133
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69ab219019c54125aa02a084
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
