BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Outdoor Adventure Apps
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260512T200000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260512T213000Z
UID:698fa9f4b48451fc3c02a1f4@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Did you know that your smartphone can enhance your outdoor exp
 eriences? This lecture introduces popular outdoor apps for all kinds of wi
 lderness adventures from hiking and biking to camping and fishing. You'll 
 learn about useful app features such as GPS navigation\, nature ID\, real-
 time updates\, and more. We'll also cover considerations for choosing apps
  and best practices regarding data and privacy.\nPresented by Meals on Whe
 els People. While all are welcome at this lecture\, the curriculum is desi
 gned for adults ages 55+.\nRegistration is required.
LOCATION:Cedar Mill Library\, Elm & Oak Room
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/698fa9f4b48451fc3c02a1f4
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Intro to Managing Your Privacy
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260414T200000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260414T213000Z
UID:698fa87c81b67dfe32a6515b@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Concerned about privacy? Unsure about accepting cookies? Come 
 learn about some essential privacy tips! In this introductory lecture\, we
 ’ll review how ads target us online\, how to limit tracking\, and where 
 to find browser settings and extensions to better control how our informat
 ion is shared. We’ll also discuss some of the key features of password m
 anagers and why they’re a safe and secure option.\nPresented by Meals on
  Wheels People. While all are welcome at this lecture\, the curriculum is 
 designed for adults ages 55+.\nRegistration is required.
LOCATION:Cedar Mill Library\, Elm & Oak Room
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/698fa87c81b67dfe32a6515b
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Virtual Program: Paintings of the American Revolution
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T010000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T020000Z
UID:697116a16724c63d00ed735a@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Virtual event - Registration required. Details will be emailed
  the day of the event.\nGarden Home Community Library is excited to be hos
 ting a presentation by art historian and educator Mallory Mortillaro. In c
 elebration of America's Semiquincentennial\, we present "Paintings of the 
 American Revolution".\nWe all know the story of the Revolutionary War\, bu
 t how much of our understanding is colored by the way the war\nwas depicte
 d by artists? Paintings of the American Revolution have been essential in 
 the way that the war was\nunderstood\, both at the time of the conflict an
 d for generations after. This lecture will explore well-known paintings\ns
 uch as Emanuel Leutze’s Washington Crossing the Delaware\, John Trumbull
 ’s Declaration of Independence\, and\nAsher Durand’s The Capture of Ma
 jor André.\nMortillaro is an art historian and educator. She has ten year
 s of teaching experience and has worked on various art research projects f
 or museums and organizations in the New York metropolitan area. She studie
 d at Drew University.
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/697116a16724c63d00ed735a
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
