DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T193000Z
UID:68a0c91bee7045528b832a58@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Build reading confidence and improve reading skills by reading
  to a dog!\nGershwin and Missy and their trainers will listen with compass
 ion and without judgment as you read.\nSign up for a 20 minute session\n.\
 nYou can bring your own book or choose one from the library shelf.\nEach t
 ime you read to Missy or Gershwin\, you will get a free book from the Frie
 nds of the Library book sale shelf. After 5 visits\, you get to choose a N
 EW book from our Read to the Dogs book box.\nThis program is for kids who 
 read by looking at the pictures to tell a story (PreK) and kids who are re
 ading words on the page.\nSign up for a session by calling 503 625-6688 or
  emailing\naskusSPL@sherwoodoregon.gov\nSession 1\n11:00 a.m. - 11:20 a.m.
 \nSession 2\n11:20 a.m.  - 11:40 a.m.\n(Break 11:40 a.m. - 11:50 a.m.)\nSe
 ssion 3\n11:50 a.m. – 12:10 p.m.\nSession 4\n12:10 p.m. - 12:30 p.m.
LOCATION:Sherwood Public Library\, Children's Area of the library
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/68a0c91bee7045528b832a58
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
