BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Chaotic Crusaders Club: Dungeons & Dragons for Teens
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260411T200000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260411T220000Z
UID:69960ae03cc3e0c9ecba0189@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Calling all adventurers! Do you want to save the day from terr
 ifying monsters\, cast powerful\, reality-bending spells\, and solve puzzl
 es and traps using your wits\, all while making new friends? Then grab you
 r dice and join us for a game of Dungeons & Dragons 5th edition. New and e
 xperienced players welcome! For teens ages 11-18. Registration is required
 .
LOCATION:Cedar Mill Library\, Upstairs Meeting Rooms
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69960ae03cc3e0c9ecba0189
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Tales to Tails
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260415T233000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260415T234500Z
UID:698e44d181b67dfe32a60a31@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Read to a certified therapy dog in a stress-free environment!\
 nSign-up for a 20-minute reading session.\nThis program will help improve 
 your child's reading skills and they get to make a new friend by reading a
 loud to a therapy dog.\nThe dogs and handlers are from\nDove Lewis Portlan
 d Area Canine Therapy Teams\nand\nPet Partners®
LOCATION:Garden Home Community Library\, Enter the building through the Re
 c Center's main entrance and walk through the building to the library and 
 check in at the front desk
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/698e44d181b67dfe32a60a31
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Digital Navigator: One-On-One Tech Help
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260410T170000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260410T210000Z
UID:6983d66bcbf6405d35665ee4@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:In a one-on-one session\, Digital Navigators can answer questi
 ons about devices\, navigating websites\, getting started with tech\, and 
 more. Digital Navigation is available in English\, Spanish\, and Arabic.\n
 Appointments are on Fridays from 10 a.m. to 2 p.m. Schedule online (\nhtt
 ps://beavertonlibrary.libcal.com/appointments?lid=3627&g=25012\n) or by c
 alling the library at 503-644-2197.
LOCATION:Beaverton City Library
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6983d66bcbf6405d35665ee4
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Drop-in Tech Help
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260317T173000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260317T190000Z
UID:688a54b9639e1e9694a3d68b@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Whether you're a beginner trying to navigate your first smartp
 hone or a more experienced user looking to troubleshoot an issue with your
  computer or assemble a custom PC build\, we’re here to help. Drop-in to
  ask questions and receive one-on-one assistance with a variety of topics\
 , including but not limited to:\nBasic computer skills (e.g. how to use a 
 mouse\, open and close programs\, create and save documents)\nSetting up a
 nd using an email account\nUsing search engines and the internet\nTransfer
 ring files and photos between devices\nBasic smartphone and tablet skills 
 (e.g. how to make a call\, send a text message\, install and use an app)\n
 No matter your level of experience\, we welcome you to join us! No registr
 ation required. Please bring your device with you if you have one\, as thi
 s will allow us to better assist you with any specific issues you may be e
 xperiencing.
LOCATION:Aloha Community Library
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/688a54b9639e1e9694a3d68b
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Paper Plane Palooza
