BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Feathered Friends Fun Day
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T170000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T200000Z
UID:698bce8e81b67dfe32a5a3c0@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:A free-family friendly drop-in event with storytimes\, a fam
 ily reading area\, free book giveaways from Garden Home Community Library
 \, arts & crafts provided by the THPRD Nature Mobile\, a scavenger hunt in
  the library\, and more. You can also learn how to decrease bird strikes o
 n your windows. In conjunction with this event we also have an\ninteractiv
 e bird walk (registration required)\n.\nSpecial bird related storytimes an
 d readings!\n*Storytime with Bakul at 10 am\n*Author Fern Wexler will read
  their book "Families of a Feather" at 11 am\nFeathered Friends Fun Day i
 s a collaboration between Garden Home Community Library and Tualatin Hills
  Parks & Recreation Department (THPRD)'s Garden Home Recreation Center to 
 celebrate birds. It's part of the nationwide Flight Path program. Flight
  Path is the first campaign in the new Spark of Science@ My Library initia
 tive. With the goal of sparking curiosity about science and creating a dee
 per understanding of how science can improve human health and the health o
 f our planet\, this initiative is a partnership between the STAR Library E
 ducation Network and HHMI Tangled Bank Studios.
LOCATION:Garden Home Community Library\, This event will be held mostly in
  the THPRD Garden Home Recreation Center Gym.
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/698bce8e81b67dfe32a5a3c0
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
