BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Teen Volunteer Club
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260416T230000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260417T000000Z
UID:68a0cf25ee7045528b832ba8@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Welcome teens 7th-12th grade who want to make a difference in 
 their community through the library!\nWe are a dedicated group of youth wh
 o seek to improve the library for all.\nProjects include:\nDecorating the 
 library for the seasons\nCreating fun craft kits for kids to Take (home) &
  Make\nBook displays and posters\nBoard game inventory\nJudging the Summer
  Reading Teen Art Contest in the spring\n...and so much more!\nWe welcome 
 newcomers!\nReach out to\naskusSPL@sherwoodoregon.gov\nto let us know you'
 re coming.\nThis club meets the first and third Thursday of the month from
  4:00 p.m. - 5:00 p.m.
LOCATION:Sherwood Public Library\, Meet at the front desk in the library.
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/68a0cf25ee7045528b832ba8
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
