END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Teen Crafternoon: Junk Journaling
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260316T233000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260317T003000Z
UID:69813b3ecbf1533ca535d8b2@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Come create a junk journal to capture all of your spring break
  memories! Junk journaling uses recycled or repurposed materials to create
  a personalized journal. It’s all about highlighting imperfections\, mak
 ing it the perfect type of journaling for both beginners and experts. Feel
  free to bring your own collage materials for your journal\, but we will h
 ave plenty of supplies to use!\nNo registration required. For teens and tw
 eens in 6th through 12th grade.
LOCATION:Aloha Community Library
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69813b3ecbf1533ca535d8b2
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Quilting Friends
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260418T170000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260418T210000Z
UID:6998c74f4a9fd98b7f7f5dee@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Are you interested in quilting for a cause? Our quilting group
  provides the fabric and invites you to quilt for St. Vincent's Hospital
 ’s Hospice program. Held every third Saturday of the month. Come and tal
 k to us!\nAre you just curious? Everyone is welcome to observe! This progr
 am is for 18+ years old\; 14+ with parent supervision.
LOCATION:Cornelius Public Library
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6998c74f4a9fd98b7f7f5dee
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Drop-in Tech Help
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260324T173000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260324T190000Z
UID:688a54b9639e1e9694a3d68c@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Whether you're a beginner trying to navigate your first smartp
 hone or a more experienced user looking to troubleshoot an issue with your
  computer or assemble a custom PC build\, we’re here to help. Drop-in to
  ask questions and receive one-on-one assistance with a variety of topics\
 , including but not limited to:\nBasic computer skills (e.g. how to use a 
 mouse\, open and close programs\, create and save documents)\nSetting up a
 nd using an email account\nUsing search engines and the internet\nTransfer
 ring files and photos between devices\nBasic smartphone and tablet skills 
 (e.g. how to make a call\, send a text message\, install and use an app)\n
 No matter your level of experience\, we welcome you to join us! No registr
 ation required. Please bring your device with you if you have one\, as thi
 s will allow us to better assist you with any specific issues you may be e
 xperiencing.
LOCATION:Aloha Community Library
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/688a54b9639e1e9694a3d68c
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
