BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:West Slope Community Library Book Group
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260506T210000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260506T223000Z
UID:693b3c4176261f28005ea7eb@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Adults meet in person monthly to discuss a featured book at th
 is \nmember-led book group. Gatherings take place in the adult nonfiction 
 \nsection of the library on the first Wednesday of the month\, 2-3:30 pm. 
 \nCheck the library calendar for details and please register if you plan \
 nto attend. All are welcome to participate! See the list of\nWest Slope Li
 brary Book Group 2026 Reads\nin the library catalog.\nJanuary 7:\nSleeping
  Giants by Rene Denfeld\n(The author plans to attend!)\nFebruary 7th: T\nh
 e Listeners by Maggie Stiefvater\nNote: March and April selections have be
 en switched because of book availability. The current\, correct selection
 s are:\nMarch 4th:\nThe Wager- a Tale of Shipwreck\, Mutiny\, and Murder b
 y David Gran\nApril 1:\nHow to read a Book by Monica Woo\nMay 6:\nAbundanc
 e by Ezra Klein\nJune 3:\nWe'll Prescribe You a Cat by Syou Ishida\nJuly 1
 :\nThe God of the Woods by Liz Moore\nAugust 5:\nThis Other Eden by Paul H
 arding\nSeptember 2:\nThe Art Spy- the Extraordinary Untold Tale of WWII R
 esistance Hero by Rose Valland\nOctober 7:\nThe\n Cure for Women- Dr. Mary
  Putnam Jacobi and the Challenge to Victorian \nMedicine That Changed Wome
 n's Lives Forever by Lydia Reeder\nNovember 4:\nThe Frozen River by Ariel 
 Lawhon\nDecember 2:\nPlayground by Richard Powers
LOCATION:West Slope Community Library
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/693b3c4176261f28005ea7eb
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Wind Down Wednesdays
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260506T170000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260506T180000Z
UID:6917a2c3886bb73600bad5bf@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Start your morning off right and join us in the Rogers Room on
  the first Wednesday of every month for a free one-hour intro level class 
 designed to help manage stress and promote well-being through progressive 
 muscle relaxation\, mindfulness\, and deep breathing. Teacher Ruby offers 
 practical tips for identifying stressors in your life\, implementing simpl
 e coping mechanisms\, and cultivating emotional survival skills that focus
  on humor and creativity. Bring your own pillow and/or mat\, wear comfy cl
 othes\, and prepare to fully unwind.\nThis class is open to adults 16 year
 s or older\, but registration is required\, and enrollment is limited to 2
 0 people.
LOCATION:Forest Grove City Library
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6917a2c3886bb73600bad5bf
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Tales to Tails
