BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:How Money Works Workshop
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T020000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T031500Z
UID:698f8f6b94297d3600ac1e07@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Learn the essential concepts from a professional financial ed
 ucator in a step-by-step roadmap that can change\nyour future. It’s time
  to discover and implement the 7 Money Milestones:\n1. Get a Financial Edu
 cation\n2. Secure Proper Protection\n3. Create an Emergency Fund\n4. Apply
  Debt Management\n5. Increase Cash Flow\n6. Build Your Wealth\n7. Protect 
 Your Wealth\nFree and open to anyone. Registration is required.
LOCATION:Garden Home Community Library\, This event will be held in the li
 brary's event room (GeRoom #7) next to the Rec Center Locker Rooms. \n\nEn
 ter via rec center's main entrance and walk through building to the librar
 y.
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/698f8f6b94297d3600ac1e07
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Digital Navigator: One-on-One Tech Help
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260507T180000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260507T184500Z
UID:698fa60a8d5e2d09335f11e7@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Get answers to your technology questions! Schedule a 45-minute
  appointment with our friendly Digital Navigator to build your digital ski
 lls. The Digital Navigator can help with installing new apps\, navigating 
 websites\, filling out online job applications\, and more.\nAppointments a
 re on Thursdays at 10am and 11am in the Bethany Library. Register online 
 or by calling 503-617-7323.\nPlease bring your own computer\, tablet\, ce
 llphone\, or e-reader with you to get assistance. Be sure to have any user
 names and passwords available for accounts you need help navigating.\nThe 
 Digital Navigator program is made possible by a partnership between Washin
 gton County Cooperative Library Services and American Connections Corps\,
  an AmeriCorps program dedicated to advancing economic prosperity by bridg
 ing the digital divide.
LOCATION:Bethany Library
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/698fa60a8d5e2d09335f11e7
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
