DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T220000Z
UID:689d3bc73bd870fbefa8102f@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Need Help Tracing Your Ancestry?\nThe Genealogical Society of 
 Washington County\, Oregon\, helps in researching lost relatives! Bring as
  much information as possible about names (including maiden names)\, birth
  dates/locations\, marriage details\, and your family tree (digital or pri
 nted). You are welcome to bring your laptop if you own one\, as there is a
 ccess to electrical outlets and free Wi-Fi. You can easily access several 
 genealogy subscription databases for free while in the library\, such as t
 he Library Edition of Ancestry.\nPre-register by Wednesday before the sess
 ion to ensure we have enough volunteers.\nEmail:\nGSWCO2123@gmail.com
LOCATION:Hillsboro Public Library\, Brookwood
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/689d3bc73bd870fbefa8102f
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Drop-in Tech Help
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260512T173000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260512T190000Z
UID:688a54b9639e1e9694a3d693@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Whether you're a beginner trying to navigate your first smartp
 hone or a more experienced user looking to troubleshoot an issue with your
  computer or assemble a custom PC build\, we’re here to help. Drop-in to
  ask questions and receive one-on-one assistance with a variety of topics\
 , including but not limited to:\nBasic computer skills (e.g. how to use a 
 mouse\, open and close programs\, create and save documents)\nSetting up a
 nd using an email account\nUsing search engines and the internet\nTransfer
 ring files and photos between devices\nBasic smartphone and tablet skills 
 (e.g. how to make a call\, send a text message\, install and use an app)\n
 No matter your level of experience\, we welcome you to join us! No registr
 ation required. Please bring your device with you if you have one\, as thi
 s will allow us to better assist you with any specific issues you may be e
 xperiencing.
LOCATION:Aloha Community Library
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/688a54b9639e1e9694a3d693
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
