DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260326T224500Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260326T231500Z
UID:69795da63cc3e0c9ecb53d11@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Do you need one-on-one assistance with your digital questions?
  A trusted guide can help you learn about home connectivity\, devices\, an
 d digital skills. Register for a slot. Bring your device or use a library 
 computer.\nRegistrants will be contacted for more details.\nSlots are 30-4
 0 minutes long. Sign up for your preferred time slot: 3\, 3:45\, 4:30\, or
  5:15. [We do not have a waitlist\; please call or visit the library the 
 day off the Digital Navigator appointment to check availability.]\nThe Dig
 ital Navigator Program (DNP) is a free service made possible by a partners
 hip between Washington County Cooperative Library Services (WCCLS) and the
  American Connections Corps\, who empowers its members and the communities
  they serve to address digital disparities and create lasting change.
LOCATION:Garden Home Community Library\, Enter through the rec center's ma
 in entrance and walk through the building to the library.
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69795da63cc3e0c9ecb53d11
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Makerspace Open Lab
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260411T170000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260411T200000Z
UID:699f9fb58b29ea2800d28bc6@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Makerspace Open Labs are for anyone who wants to check out the
  space and use our equipment to make cool things. Room assistants are avai
 lable to guide you in the basic use of the tools and technology. Come in w
 ith an idea and leave with a finished project! For more information about 
 the Makerspace and its resources\,\nsee here\n.\nMakerspace Open Labs take
  place on the following weekly schedule:\nTuesdays\n\, 5:30 - 7:30PM\nThur
 sdays\n\, 4:00 - 6:00PM\nSaturdays\n\, 10:00 AM - 1:00PM\nSundays\n\, 1:30
  - 5:30P\nEach month we provide the materials\, tools and instructions for
  a featured Makerspace project that everyone is invited to try.\nApril's f
 eatured project is Seed Paper (pictured).\nIMPORTANT:\nAdults using the M
 akerspace for the first time need to\nsign a waiver\n\; people under the a
 ge of 18 must have a waiver signed by a parent or guardian.\nYou can sign 
 and submit waivers online here.
LOCATION:Tualatin Public Library\, Makerspace
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/699f9fb58b29ea2800d28bc6
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
