SUMMARY:Digital Navigator Tech Help
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260320T001500Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260320T004500Z
UID:69795d34834cbb3dea29c9f2@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Do you need one-on-one assistance with your digital questions?
  A trusted guide can help you learn about home connectivity\, devices\, an
 d digital skills. Register for a slot. Bring your device or use a library 
 computer.\nRegistrants will be contacted for more details.\nSlots are 30-4
 0 minutes long. Sign up for your preferred time slot: 3\, 3:45\, 4:30\, or
  5:15. [We do not have a waitlist\; please call or visit the library the 
 day off the Digital Navigator appointment to check availability.]\nThe Dig
 ital Navigator Program (DNP) is a free service made possible by a partners
 hip between Washington County Cooperative Library Services (WCCLS) and the
  American Connections Corps\, who empowers its members and the communities
  they serve to address digital disparities and create lasting change.
LOCATION:Garden Home Community Library\, Enter via the rec center's main d
 oors and walk through the building to the library.
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69795d34834cbb3dea29c9f2
