BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Writer's Group: Workshop - Unlock Your Writing: Using Tarot to Dee
 pen the Creative Process
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260429T013000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260429T023000Z
UID:69b0d8101e64afd01e6146d3@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:This is a virtual meeting. Registrants will receive all detail
 s.\nUnlock Your Writing: Using Tarot to Deepen the Creative Process with M
 eg Hayertz\nWhether you have a deep relationship with the Tarot\, or have 
 never pulled a card\, this workshop offers simple techniques for reading o
 urselves\, our blocks\, and the messages in our creative works. When we st
 op succumbing to our challenges or bulldozing through them\, and instead l
 isten to our creative blocks\, we find inspiration\, motivation\, and mome
 ntum in our creative practice. What would it be like to draft\, revise\, a
 nd complete a project without losing connection with yourself or with the 
 energy that guides you? Come find out! In this workshop\, you will gain in
 sight and momentum around a creative challenge or block. All genres and sk
 ill levels welcome. Tarot cards will be provided.\nAbout our presenter:\nM
 eg Hayertz\n(she/they) is the author of\nTarot for Beginners\n(Althea Pres
 s) and the founder of Creative Momentum\, where she helps writers free the
 ir voice\, nourish their practice\, and finish their project. She holds an
  MFA from California Institute of Integral Studies and her fiction has app
 eared in\nThe Louisville Review\n\,\nCALYX\n\,\nPress Pause\, VoiceCatcher
 \n\, and elsewhere. She lives in Portland\, Oregon with her partner and ca
 t. Visit her at\nwww.CreativeMomentum.art\nand on YouTube\n@MakeItMeanIt
LOCATION:Garden Home Community Library\, This is a virtual meeting. Detail
 s will be emailed to registrants.
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b0d8101e64afd01e6146d3
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Bricks for Better Brains Monthly Social
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260326T213000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260326T230000Z
UID:697114f24a9fd98b7f78da94@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Bricks for Better Brains© encourages older people to explore 
 creativity\, strengthen social connections\, and take advantage of tactile
  stimulation.\nParticipants will work on a set or free build. All material
 s will be provided.\nAbout our presenter and the founder of Bricks for Bet
 ter Brains: Natalia Kasperovich is a university-educated chemical engineer
 \, community volunteer\, educator\, and most importantly\, a lifelong lear
 ner. She recently earned the Associate Degree in Gerontology from Portland
  Community College. She is a passionate advocate for continuous and self-m
 otivated learning\, intergenerational understanding\, diversity\, and incl
 usivity.
LOCATION:Garden Home Community Library
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/697114f24a9fd98b7f78da94
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
