BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Truth and AI: Misinformation\, Deepfakes\, and the Digital World
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260403T010000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260403T020000Z
UID:69adfdd34dacf581ff80841b@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:AI can create photos\, videos\, and stories that look real but
  aren’t\, so how do you know what’s real online anymore? Learn how the
 se tricks work\, why they spread so quickly\, and practice spotting the si
 gns of misinformation before it fools you. This session will help you shar
 pen your skills to recognize misleading content\, understand how deepfakes
  are made\, and learn practical strategies for separating fact from fictio
 n in your daily digital life.\nRegistration is encouraged\, but not requir
 ed.\nPresenter Bio:\nCrystal Trice has over 20 years of experience in libr
 aries and education and is the founder of\nScissors & Glue\, LLC\n. She le
 ads interactive trainings and workshops on topics ranging from project man
 agement to artificial intelligence\, helping libraries and schools spark p
 ositive change. Based near Portland\, Oregon\, Crystal enjoys life with he
 r husband\, a small menagerie of farm animals\, and an endless supply of s
 ticky notes and colorful pens.
LOCATION:Sherwood Public Library
