BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Solve Problems\, Lead Teams\, Drive Results: Why Project Managemen
 t?
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260313T020000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260313T030000Z
UID:696febb530cbd582eff59438@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Interested in a career in project management? Join the Portlan
 d Chapter of the Project Management Institute for a hands-on exploration o
 f what project management is\, why it’s essential across industries\, an
 d share real-world case studies that highlight the impact of great project
  leadership. You’ll also learn practical steps to start your journey - a
 nd there will be plenty of time to ask questions and talk about your own p
 rojects. Take the first step toward a rewarding new path!\nOpen to teens a
 nd adults.  Pizza and beverages will be provided.  Please register using 
 the link at the top of this page.\nPresented by Elizabeth Cychosz Johnson
 \, MA\, PMP\, Director of Community Outreach for the Project Management In
 stitute - Portland Chapter\, which promotes the profession of project mana
 gement by creating a culture and community that facilitates professional g
 rowth through education and volunteerism.
LOCATION:Aloha Community Library
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/696febb530cbd582eff59438
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
