BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Creations with Carralez
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260418T200000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260418T220000Z
UID:69a6453d403a4e5652de014c@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Creations with Carralez is a free mixed media art class for ad
 ults that explores different creative techniques. This month\, we’ll be 
 focusing on florals and poetry\, blending watercolor and pen to create exp
 ressive\, layered artwork inspired by flowers and meaningful words. No exp
 erience is needed—beginners are welcome. All supplies are provided and r
 egistration is required. Class size is limited to 20 to ensure a supportiv
 e\, engaging atmosphere for everyone.\nAbout Your Teachers\n:\nDanielle Ca
 rralez is a self-taught painter with over a decade of experience\, working
  in both watercolor\, acrylic\, and more. Art has been a personal journey 
 of growth\, expression\, and healing for sharing with others. She's paired
  with the quirky Mrs. Kristin\, whose creativity and heart for people make
  every space brighter. Their shared love for community\, art\, and writing
  has inspired them to step out and spread their skills and compassion\, cr
 eating welcoming spaces where others feel encouraged to explore and create
 .
LOCATION:Forest Grove City Library
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69a6453d403a4e5652de014c
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
