DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260317T171500Z
UID:6941ffc6c967cb41207d31ee@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Welcome infants 0-12 months and their caregivers!\nAttending B
 aby Storytime is a great way to build the bond between child and adult.\nI
 n this program you and your baby will sing songs\, play action rhymes\, an
 d grow together with books.\n15 minutes of playtime for babies and convers
 ation time for adults follow each session.\nThis is the winter session of 
 this program and it runs January 6 - January 27 & March 3 - 17.\nBaby Stor
 ytime takes a break March 24\, 2026.\nA special program for children 0-6 w
 ill be held February 3-24\, 2026. See February 2026 entry.\nArrive anytime
  between 9:30a.m. - 10:00a.m. to enjoy this program. We understand how dif
 ficult it is to be punctual with a baby. Playtime is just as beneficial as
  the storytime.\nLibrary opens at 10:00 a.m.\nFor more information about y
 our infant's development\, we recommend the CDC (Centers for Disease Contr
 ol) Website.\nInfants
LOCATION:Sherwood Public Library\, Community Room\, first floor.
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6941ffc6c967cb41207d31ee
