UID:6942044bddf5632800213d57@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Welcome toddlers 12 months - 24 months and their caregivers!\n
 Attending Fun for Ones Storytime is a great way to build the bond between 
 child and adult.\nIn this program you and your toddler will sing songs\, p
 lay action rhymes\, and grow together with books.\n20 minutes of playtime 
 for kids and conversation time for adults follows each session.\nThis is t
 he winter session of this program and it runs January 6 - January 27 & Mar
 ch 3 - March 17\, 2026.\nFun for Ones Storytime takes a break  March 24. S
 pring Session of Fun for Ones will begin March 31\, 2026.\nSpecial Note: F
 ebruary Fun for Ones will pause to bring a special music program for ages 
 0-6. See February calendar entry.\nArrive anytime between 10:15 a.m. - 11:
 00a.m. to enjoy this program. We understand how difficult it is to be punc
 tual with a toddler. Playtime is just as beneficial as the storytime.\nFor
  more information about your child's development\, we recommend the CDC (C
 enters for Disease Control) Website.\nDevelopmental Milestones\n1 Year\n15
  months\n18 months\n2 years
