DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T220000Z
UID:6943200e6f926136000b7437@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Need assistance with housing\, clothing\, food\, or rent? Look
 ing for health care\, job support\, or simply want someone to talk to? Eve
 ryone is welcome! Join us for our drop-in hours: Wednesdays from 1 PM to 
 3 PM & Fridays from 4 PM to 6 PM Don't miss this chance to connect with r
 esources and community support.\n¿Necesitas ayuda con la vivienda\, la ro
 pa\, la comida o la renta? ¿Buscas atención médica\, apoyo laboral o si
 mplemente quiere hablar con alguien? ¡Todos son bienvenidos! Visítanos 
 nuestro horario los miércoles de 1 p.m. a 3 p.m. y viernes de 4 p.m. a 6 
 p.m. No pierdas la oportunidad de conectarte con recursos y apoyo comunit
 ario.
LOCATION:Cornelius Public Library
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6943200e6f926136000b7437
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:OMSI Science Pub: Fault Lines to Lifelines: Preparedness for Casca
 dia’s Earthquakes and Tsunamis
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T020000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T040000Z
UID:698bb24c4dacf581ff7a6dc0@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:What would a major Cascadia earthquake and tsunami mean for ou
 r communities—and how can we prepare now? Join Oregon State University e
 xperts Jenna Tilt and Felicia Olmeta Schult for an engaging lecture & Q&A 
 session about the science\, risks\, and human dimensions of Cascadia’s m
 ost significant natural hazards. Drawing on research and on-the-ground com
 munity work\, they’ll explore how earthquakes and tsunamis impact people
  and places\, what resilience really looks like\, and the practical steps 
 individuals and communities can take to turn fault lines into lifelines. C
 ome for the science\, stay for the strategies—and leave better prepared 
 for what lies beneath and beyond our coast. Refreshments and mocktails fro
 m Urban River Spirits will be provided.\nPlease register with OMSI to save
  your spot.\nScience Pub: Cascadia Earthquakes: From Risk to Readiness —
  OMSI\nThis program is part of Hillsboro Reads.
LOCATION:Hillsboro Public Library\, Brookwood
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/698bb24c4dacf581ff7a6dc0
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
