BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:What Does It Mean To Be An American
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260507T010000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260507T023000Z
UID:698679bb8d5e2d09335d9bce@wccls.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:This conversation will explore when and how we define ourselve
 s as an “American.” Does knowing the Constitution make us American? Do
 es living on land controlled by the United States of America make us Ameri
 can? Through conversation and nonverbal exploration\, we will share what 
 “American” means to us individually and within the communities we belo
 ng to or came from\, and what perspectives shaped our understanding of Ame
 rican identity and who is included in “We the People.”\nChisao Hata is
  a performing artist\, educator\, and arts integration specialist. She has
  been called a “community weaver” through facilitation\, community eng
 agement and creating artistic collaborations.\nRegistration is required. I
 f you need assistance registering\, please contact library staff.
LOCATION:Cedar Mill Library\, Elm and Oak Room
URL:https://wccls.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/698679bb8d5e2d09335d9bce
X-SOURCE:WCCLS Libraries
END:VEVENT
